g”. Working from a systematisation and critique of previous attempts to develop a theory, it proposes a modelling of memory and remembering centred on the connection between modern media developments and social processes of remembering.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 0aMass mediaxPsychological aspects. 0aMemoryxSocial aspects. 0aMemoryxSociological aspects. 0aSocial perceptionxPhilosophy. 4aErinnerung. 4aGedächtnis. 4aKulturwissenschaften. 4aMassenmedium. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aMemory.  acultural studies.  amass media.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Literary and Cultural Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110637854oZDB-23-GLC08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2008z9783110212129oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET LINGUISTIK UND LITERATURWISSENSCHAFT  2008z9783110209457oZDB-23-DGA0 cprintz978311018983440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311020210640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110202106423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110202106/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGAb2008  aZDB-23-DGGb2008  aZDB-23-GLCc2000d2014